cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.CR 

The paper deals with person re-identification, which is a computer vision problem. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also extensively uses deep learning technologies, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as well. Additionally, the paper involves metric learning, which could place it in cs.MM (Multimedia). The use of angular discriminative loss and triplet loss could suggest that the paper belongs to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper also deals with security and privacy, which could place it in cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
